Anonymous Fri 03 Jun 2022 07:19:56 No.48227928 Report
Quoted By:
>>48227390
Second-person format is optional, and not the problem - the problem primarily is syntax, descriptive writing, and lazy sounding word-choice.

For example: ">The locker next to mine is open and a short cheetah girl is right next to me. Big hoop earings hang off rounded ears, and purple eye makeup is on her kinda droopy eyes. As my eyes go down I notice she's wearing a really baggy and open hoodie, which bunches up around her neck and wrists over a pink v-neck shirt and a really short pair of shorts. She's also not wearing any shoes. A quick scan and I notice that none of them are wearing shoes, just walking around barefoot."

Besides the typo on "Earrings", this whole paragraph is a pretty good example on how awkward you write your character's observations; the descriptors come off as lazy and not very well-thought-out. A way I personally would've written it would've been something like:

>In front of the open locker next to mine stands a female anthro-cheetah on the shorter end of her species' height-spectrum. One of the first things I notice about what she's wearing are her obnoxiously-sized gold hoop-earrings that hang low from her henry's pocket; the look she's giving me from her purple-lidded eyes is increasingly unnerving as they light up a bit the more she scans me.

>Her choice of wardrobe is fitting of her sloppily-applied makeup, wearing an oversized, "I borrowed this from my boyfriend" zip-up hoodie and pink V-neck combo with black gym-shorts that I know barely pass the school dress-code. The oddest part to me though is the fact she's completely forgone any kind of footwear. In a school this dirty!

Some of the things I added descriptors to might've been inaccurate to what you had imagined, but I'm working off of my own assumptions and add-ins to what is pretty barebones in terms of descriptive writing.

I apologize if this comes off as harsh, but my only intention is to help you out on future stuff. Hope to see you post more stuff.
